<html><head></head><body dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: =
after-white-space;"><p>Hi Grant,</p><p>I am following up on our visit to =
the property on Tuesday. I left the meeting feeling quite confused about =
several points, and I would be grateful if you could please clarify the =
following so I can properly understand the approach Tower is =
taking:</p><p><b>1. Independent expert testing</b></p><p>You indicated =
that Tower/you will not pay for any expert testing as part of my =
preparation of the claim, as you said that is what you are already =
doing. However, I am struggling to understand this position. =46rom my =
perspective, you are preparing the claim from Tower=E2=80=99s side, and =
I have not been invited to or involved in any of the NZRSC assessments =
or discussions. This does not feel independent or transparent from my =
side. Could you please clarify why Tower would not cover the costs of me =
engaging my own independent experts (e.g., engineers, hygienists), =
particularly given the seriousness of the fire and the chemical =
involvement?</p><p><b>2. Structural elements =E2=80=93 linings and =
framing</b></p><p>You mentioned replacing only a couple of beams and =
using methods such as dry ice blasting and thermal fogging for the =
bricks. Could you please clarify how this is considered adequate given =
that:</p><p><ul class=3D"MailOutline"><li>Smoke odour and residue remain =
even on the first floor =E2=80=94 the least affected part of the house =
=E2=80=94 more than three months after the fire, which suggests deep =
penetration.</li><li>The fire was electrical in origin but also involved =
spa chemicals, meaning corrosive residues (chlorides, bromides) are =
highly likely to have penetrated linings, framing, and =
fixings,</li><li>Painting over materials or superficial cleaning does =
not appear to restore the property to an =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D =
standard.</li><li>The suggested treatments do not seem to reasonably =
reinstate &nbsp;to an =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard, particularly =
given the dieppe smoke and chemical =
penetration</li><li><b><br></b></li><li><b><br></b></li><li><br></li></ul>=
</p><ul class=3D"MailOutline"><li><b>3. Roof =
assessment</b></li></ul><p>You indicated that the roof requires no work. =
I find this difficult to reconcile with the evidence:</p><p><ul =
class=3D"MailOutline"><li>Large volumes of black smoke were seen coming =
out from all sides of the roof during the fire.</li><li>A gutter was =
significantly heat-damaged.</li><li>Local reporting even suggested the =
fire appeared to be in the roof.</li></ul></p><p>=46rom my =
understanding, if heat was sufficient to damage guttering externally, =
then the roof cavity, insulation, underlay, battens, fixings, and =
trusses may also have been affected. Could you please clarify what =
inspection method was used to conclude the roof was undamaged? Were any =
cavity inspections, residue tests, or intrusive checks carried =
out?</p><p><b>4. Services =E2=80=93 gas, electricity, and =
water</b></p><p>I understand that you are going to test the gas unit and =
propose a plan to bring it up to new standard, which I appreciate. =
However, could you also please clarify what is planned for the =
&nbsp;electricty system, which suffered significant and widespread =
damage and the water distribution system</p><p>At present I am unclear =
how these critical services will be properly tested and =
reinstated.</p><p><b>5. Timing and completeness of =
assessments</b></p><p>I am also confused that you seem to already be =
forming a plan for repairs when assessments have not been completed and =
I have not yet seen any NZRSC or other formal report. Could you please =
clarify why a repair plan is being discussed at this stage, rather than =
waiting for the full results of intrusive testing and reporting, =
considering some/many test still needs to be performed?</p><p><b>6. =
Testing and reporting</b></p><p>Could you please confirm:</p><p><ul =
class=3D"MailOutline"><li>What tests or assessments have actually been =
completed so far?</li><li>Why, given the involvement of spa chemicals, =
no intrusive testing has been arranged?</li><li>When the NZRSC report =
and other reports will be made available to me?</li></ul></p><p><b>7. =
Accommodation support</b></p><p data-start=3D"286" data-end=3D"658">At =
present, my rental accommodation is being covered under the contents =
policy ($30,000 limit). However, the house remains uninhabitable, and =
the time taken to complete assessments and progress reinstatement has =
been prolonged. These delays are not of my making, yet they directly =
extend the period in which I am unable to live in my home.</p><p>The =
Fair Insurance Code makes it clear that insurers must act fairly and not =
leave customers worse off through delay. The underlying principle of =
insurance is to restore the insured to the position they were in before =
the loss. On that basis, could you please confirm whether Tower will =
provide additional accommodation support under the house policy, or =
otherwise extend cover, so that I am not unfairly disadvantaged by =
circumstances outside of my control?</p><p><b>8. Privacy Act =
material</b></p><p>You previously referred me to information provided =
under the Privacy Act, but the links I received do not open or function. =
Could you please resend this information, ensuring that the links are =
accessible, or alternatively provide the documents as direct PDF/email =
attachments?</p><p>I would greatly appreciate your clarification on each =
of these points so that I can properly understand how my home will be =
restored to a safe, =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard.</p><p>Kind =
regards,</p><p>Raffaella del Prete</p><div><br></div><div =
class=3D"AppleOriginalContents" style=3D"direction: ltr;"><blockquote =
